813
00:52:38,161 --> 00:52:45,899
Scott: I think the thing is, in those early games, I was trying to play safe, but I wasn't playing safe because I didn't understand how to play safe.

814
00:52:46,201 --> 00:52:46,703
Rym: And

815
00:52:46,744 --> 00:53:09,140
Scott: I just explained how to play safe is to just realize, there are five of each card, if you ditch one at the start or the end, then all other cards of that number are safe, as long as you don't hurt yourself by desuiting a color too early, then you know which, you can separate your hand into the numbers that could paradox and the numbers that can't paradox.

816
00:53:09,180 --> 00:53:17,010
